Based on the provided excerpts, the requirements are as follows:

**Automatic Actions for Exceeded Logon Attempts (Requirement 03.01.08):**
When the maximum number of unsuccessful attempts is exceeded, SP 800-171r3 requirement 03.01.08 requires organizations to automatically take one or more of the following selected actions:
* Lock the account or node for an organization-defined time period [1];
* Lock the account or node until released by an administrator [1];
* Delay the next logon prompt [1];
* Notify the system administrator [1]; or
* Take another organization-defined action [1].

**Required Training (Requirement 03.02.01):**
Requirement 03.02.01 requires organizations to provide security literacy training to system users that covers:
* Initial training for new users and at an organization-defined frequency thereafter [3];
* Training when required by system changes or following organization-defined events [3]; and
* Training on recognizing and reporting indicators of insider threat, social engineering, and social mining [3].
